by <a href="/contributor/tien-tzuo/" title="Posts by Tien Tzuo" onclick="s_objectID='river_author';" rel="author">Tien Tzuo</a> </div>

<p class="excerpt">In the wake of Prince&#8217;s untimely death, more and more stories have been revealed about his secret life of good works: anonymous checks, civil rights activism, charity concerts, etc. But I&#8217;d like to talk about something else &#8212; the NPG Music Club, an online subscription music club founded on Valentine&#8217;s Day 2001 as a virtual love letter to Prince&#8217;s many fans. <a href="http://techcrunch.com/2016/05/21/how-prince-and-bowie-started-streaming-music-services/" class="read-more" data-omni-sm="gbl_river_readmore,6">Read&nbsp;More</a></p>

<h2 class="post-title"><a href="http://techcrunch.com/2016/05/20/flashfunders-relaunches-with-crowdfunding-support-with-the-pass-of-title-iii-of-the-jobs-act/" data-omni-sm="gbl_river_headline,18">FlashFunders relaunches with crowdfunding support with the pass of Title III of the JOBS&nbsp;Act</a></h2>
<div class="byline">
<time datetime="2016-05-20 12:09:07" class="timestamp">
yesterday </time>
by <a href="/author/jordan-crook/" title="Posts by Jordan Crook" onclick="s_objectID='river_author';" rel="author">Jordan Crook</a> </div>

<p class="excerpt">In the wake of the passing of Title III of the JOBS Act, crowdfunding equity platform FlashFunders has relaunched its site with new features.
The new features allow users to crowdfund investment under Form C, which allows for up to $1 million in a single Series from anyone, not just accredited investors.
FlashFunders launched on the scene a little under one year ago, offering a web-only way&hellip; <a href="http://techcrunch.com/2016/05/20/flashfunders-relaunches-with-crowdfunding-support-with-the-pass-of-title-iii-of-the-jobs-act/" class="read-more" data-omni-sm="gbl_river_readmore,18">Read&nbsp;More</a></p>

<h2 class="post-title"><a href="http://techcrunch.com/2016/05/20/paul-bragiel-is-back-with-a-new-venture-firm/" data-omni-sm="gbl_river_headline,19">Paul Bragiel is back with a new venture&nbsp;firm</a></h2>
<div class="byline">
<time datetime="2016-05-20 11:59:49" class="timestamp">
yesterday </time>
by <a href="/author/connie-loizos/" title="Posts by Connie Loizos" onclick="s_objectID='river_author';" rel="author">Connie Loizos</a> </div>

<p class="excerpt">Paul Bragiel, the venture capitalist who made an unsuccessful run at qualifying for the Sochi 2014 Winter Olympics as lone member of the Colombian cross-country ski team, is forming a new, San Francisco-based venture firm with his brother, Dan. According to an SEC filing, they are targeting $10 million for their debut effort. The outfit is called Bragiel Brothers.
We&#8217;ve reached out&hellip; <a href="http://techcrunch.com/2016/05/20/paul-bragiel-is-back-with-a-new-venture-firm/" class="read-more" data-omni-sm="gbl_river_readmore,19">Read&nbsp;More</a></p>

function hideShowTbJumpToTop() {
var total_width = 0;
// Calculate total width taken by items minus our button to see if it'll
// overlap with other toolbar menus.
jQuery( '#wp-admin-bar-root-default > li' ).each( function() {
var self = jQuery( this );
if ( 'wp-admin-bar-jumptotop-button-menu' != self.attr( 'id' ) )
total_width += self.width();
});
if ( jQuery( '#wp-admin-bar-jumptotop-button-menu' ).position()['left'] - total_width < 10 ) {
jQuery( '#jumptotop' ).animate( { 'top': '-50px' }, 'fast' );
} else if ( jQuery( window ).scrollTop() >= 350 && parseInt( jQuery( '#jumptotop' ).css( 'top' ) ) < 0 ) {

jQuery( '#jumptotop' ).animate( { 'top': '-50px' }, 'fast' );
}
}
// handle on page load if auto scrolling to a position

clearTimeout( jumpToTopTimer );
jumpToTopTimer = setTimeout( jumpToTopRefresh, 150 );
} );
